Rating Comment:
This was my second time using Urban Mop. 
1. I was asked to reschedule from my chosen time at 9 am to 2 pm a week before my appt. which I did. 
2. The afternoon before I was asked to change from 2 pm to 11 am. which I did not. 
3. Both times I was told it was to accommodate Ashley, who was my cleaner for the first appointment with Urban Mop. 
4. The day of my cleaning it was not Ashley who arrived. It was Jamps. I was not notified of this change in cleaners at all. 
5. I was also not notified that my cleaning would now be done over four hours with one cleaner rather than two hours with two cleaners like I had requested and fully expected as that was my experience the first time. 
6. I had requested female cleaners and instead a male cleaner arrived. 
7. I had to work at staying out of the way of the cleaner over four hours instead of two. I would have never requested a four hour clean but Urban Mop put me in this awkward position on the spot without any advance notice. 
8. Apparently they hadn’t prepared the cleaner either because he was surprised to learn he would be doing a four hour clean alone. It was awkward for both of us and I had to deal with how to move forward. 
9. I had purchased Christmas chocolates for Ashley and one other female cleaner. Instead I gave one box to Jamps, a person I had not met and was left with a second one, not given. 
10. I had emailed Urban Mop in between my first and second cleaning appointments with detailed instructions as to what I wanted done differently at the second appointment. It didn’t matter because I had to retell these instructions to the new cleaner myself anyway. My email proved to have been a waste of time. 
11. Both cleanings left room for improvement. Although Jamps did a better job overall, rinsing out the flat mop cloth as he went and using a different mop and cleaner for tile and wood floors as I had requested. With the first cleaning one flat mop cloth was used for the entire house, and only on one side when it could have at least been flipped over to a second side to continue the cleaning. I wonder about the quality of training for the cleaners. 
12. I am not sure at all about booking Urban Mop for a third clean. I don’t think they can accommodate my wishes. Two female cleaners for a two hour clean every month at a 9 am  appointment and leave me with the feeling that my house has been well cleaned. No surprises and no last minute changes without notice. I can understand the occasional need to switch things up but this second appointment was very mishandled.
Services: Three Bedroom Home**, 2 x Full Bathrooms*, 1 x Half Bathrooms

Again, it was good and no real complaints, I just think for over 200 dollars I should be wowed!!

Rating Comment:
Hi,

I am cancelling your future cleaning services at 12 Westmeath Crescent, 14 Peikoff Crescent, 24 Rutherglen Terrace etc. I also request for refund the cleaning charges or provide me a two-hour cleaning services by providing right people. I had shared with you pictures and video and even after that you charge, which I am not happy about your services. Liz did not clean anything at home. She does not know how to clean. She pours so many chemicals in kitchen area where people normally cook. She only spends time in kitchen for entire two hours and created mess which took me another 30 minutes to clean entire kitchen. In two hours, you can do below.

30 minutes - Main washroom in 2nd floor
15 minutes - Powder washroom
30 minutes - Kitchen
15 minutes - front entrance
30 minutes - hallway and steps

In the past many people cleaned many areas listed above including some of the good people from your company.

I had told many times the priority as below order.
1. Cleaning washrooms - two or more washroom when required
2. Moping Kitchen floor, hall ways
3. Cleaning front entrance and mop it

I need one cleaner, who comes regularly to meet the expectation. I don't want you to send new faces every week.

I don't need any cleaning services from you in future unless you change your process as I requested above. I found most time your new people never clean washroom. Even last time I had asked Liz to clean washroom. She had 15 minutes. She did not even clean toilet bowl, which I can clean under 5 minutes.

In the past I had some good people like listed below. I found good people don't stay with you. Looks like they are not happy with you. In future if you want to have business refund me the last two hours. Assign one person and provide the required cleaning in the assigned time slot as listed above.

1. Bonnie
2. JC


Regards,
Ragulan

Rating Comment: I selected deep clean and a few additional options (inside oven clean etc.) for our monthly house cleaning. The first time we had our house cleaned, my husband and I were really frustrated. The cleaner said they were finished (4-5 hours early) and asked us to check each room to sign off. It took 2s to realize this person didn't dust entire rooms, completely missed cleaning the kitchen countertop and backsplash and started to use water to clean our antique wood furniture to name just a few issues. We pointed out all of these things - they went back to make the updates and asked us to recheck only for us to discover other sections of rooms completely missed (tv coffee table had not been dusted or wiped, upstairs master bedroom dresser had not been dusted or wiped etc.). The list went on. It was a frustrating experience, but the cleaner ultimately went back with a lot of oversight and direction from our end (which was time out of our busy work days) and the house looked and smelled great upon completion. As a result, we didn't leave a negative review and provided a tip because despite how much oversight and back and forth was required, this person ultimately left our house looking great. Fast forward to yesterday when our house was cleaned again as we had signed up for your monthly cleaning service. My husband and I decided to try again and see if having our house cleaned with your service would be better the second time. I tried to research your company's definition of a deep clean since you charge extra for it on your website, but couldn't find anything online. As a result of our cleaner telling us that because we hadn't selected a box on your website that would let them move pictures etc. to dust or provided specific guidance on which items to clean (despite selecting deep clean on your website and being charged extra for that), I typed up a full list of what a deep clean meant from our perspective for each room in the house based on market research from other companies. I also reconfirmed there was no supposed box on your booking system to check to allow our cleaner to move pictures and made sure to include a typed up note that this was okay in our booking and once again verbally reiterated this point when the cleaner arrived. The same cleaner arrived to provide another "deep clean" of our house. This time it went a little better, however their attention to detail and care was still deficient. When mopping floors, they didn't lift up small floor mats, but simply mopped around them instead. They completely missed an entire area of the house to vacuum, mop and clean. The kitchen counter tops (which were once again left as clear as possible for our cleaner and only had our Nespresso coffee machine, knife block and toaster left on them) had been cleaned around these items (underneath the coffee machine was still dirty from coffee that had spilled). I had selected a box to have our walls spot cleaned, but only noticed they had spot cleaned walls in one area of our house. The inside shower tiles had not been cleaned because, "your shower head is not detachable". I am not sure what a deep clean means for your company, but this was another very frustrating and disappointing experience. Once all of these things were pointed out, the person went back and corrected them and the house once again looked and smelled amazing upon them leaving. However, the amount of time, effort, oversight and frustration to achieve the result is not worth the price charged. Very disappointed as your company has such positive reviews online and we have never had a problem with a cleaning service in the past. I have given a yellow OK face as a rating because our house was left clean and smelling great each time, but the amount of oversight and frustration required to get there is not worth it. We would be willing to have our house cleaned one more time by your company with a different cleaner. However, if this is not an option, my husband and I will have to cancel and book with another company.

Rating Comment: Based on the reviews of others, I had high hopes for the services of this company. The task was to clean a completely empty 2-level townhouse, prior to it being listed for sale, and following top to bottom painting and miscellaneous handyman jobs. I provided a very specific list of items, which they assured me would be done and that none of these items were an issue.  Cleaners arrived on time at 9:00 a.m., a very good sign. Later I received a call and email that the cleaners had to leave to go to another client, but that a supervisor would come to finish the job and check the work at 4:00 pm - no problem. But when the real estate agent sent me pics of a new front door mat I noticed that the front door brass plate and windows were not clean, something I had specifically asked for. I called urban mop to find out why and was told “we only clean inside.” I had also asked that all inside windows be cleaned, and it now seems this wasn’t done either…so much for inside cleaning only and honoring requests. I still am waiting to hear why they didn’t tell me they wouldn’t do the things I had asked for. For all of this I paid almost $400, which wouldn’t be an issue if they’d delivered what I thought I was paying for. None of my requests were unreasonable, all basic stuff, which they claimed they would do. Now I just feel ripped off and extremely disappointed. I’d go elsewhere another time.

Rating Comment:
Sadly I have to say the level of service seems to have gone down hill recently. We have always liked Urban Mop but the last two times I have hired Urban Mop I have not been impressed. The time before this was absolutely unacceptable and I appreciate that Urban Mop customer service rectified the situation. I gave it another chance and this time on Sunday it wasn’t as bad, but it was only mediocre. We were moving out of the house that day and luckily we didn’t pack our vacuum yet because the cleaner did not bring his own. All of the furniture had already been removed so there was nothing in the way, and yet there was still dust all along the baseboards in the bedrooms where he was to vacuum and dust. The kitchen sink also still had bits of food in it and I don’t think the powder room was cleaned at all. 

We did not have the time to go through all of the issues with the cleaner as we were in a rush to move out and just had to accept it and move on to other things. But we will likely look to a different cleaning company in the future.

Rating Comment:
Very disappointed… this was not a hard apartment to clean. Floors are tiled and were not cleaned under the 2 beds. Lumps of hair, dust, leftovers empty gum packs etc found under the beds, i had to pass the mop under the beds. Same for under the bathroom small sink cabinet: was not cleaned… I was told by Lisa that they’re not supposed to move furniture?  Passing my mop under the bed there after did not involve moving furniture. I found a feminine pad there stuck to the floor along with clumps of hair which I cleaned myself (was easily reachable). Onside of Oven had not been cleaned until i brought it up during quick brief inspection of the space. Glassed shower doors had not been cleaned from soap scum (I was told they had been with «  scrubbing bubbles » which is one of our products left on site (and was not supposed to be used by cleaning crew as they are supposed to supply their own) … After i was able to demo how i got the glass clean in one corner by simply scrubbing a bit harder with my own sponge, I asked Lisa to please re-clean the est of the glasses doors, which she proceeded in doing. After she left, i ended up redoing it all myself for glass to come clear again. I had emptied the fridge-freezer from containers night prior but , despite fridge having been wiped, the freezer  had obviously not been wiped as there small pieces of frozen foods left inside the pull out drawers. That was a narrow compact very easy freezer compartment to clean. 
Also, despite relieving the crew from having to wash linens as i did this night prior, entire duvet was thrown into washer causing it to be unbalanced and not draining. However, i was able to resolve this by coming on site and Lisa was very accommodating in staying later until it dried, after putting it in the dryer. At the end, I ended up remaking the bed as i had Lisa focus in cleaning again the shower doors and the sink (which i was able to unclog).
I can forgive the duvet being thrown by mistake in the wash and causing the washer to be unbalanced and me having to come on site to resolve, but i was extremely disappointed with the lack of cleaning in obvious areas (oven until i pointed out, under the beds where i was told they’re not supposed to move furniture, under the sink cabinet (easily accessible), window ledge was not dusted either, i ended up getting thise shower doors clean residue free after Lisa had left. Very disappointed

Rating Comment:
Cleaner has been by twice, and each time it is evident that the cleaner is not thorough: 
1. the cleaner is in a rush to get elsewhere
2. the cleaner's done the "bare minimum", i.e. it is evident that the hardwood floors and tiles on the main floor were not mopped; the kitchen counters were not wiped/cleaned; the toilet seats were not cleaned; windowsills/ledges unattended; stainless steel surfaces similarly not wiped down/cleaned, etc. 

There is too much variation in cleaning from cleaner to cleaner which makes the quality of the service very unpredictable and affects client satisfaction. The cleaner did not do a deep clean as I booked, the whole job took only 2 1/2 - 3 hours vs 5 1/2 hrs.  The outside of the kitchen cupboards were not cleaned. I also believe that the floors were mopped without removing the dirt beforehand. The cleaner showed up an hour early, luckily I was home.
I don't think the cleaner knew what I booked as he was cleaning things that are considered as extras (i.e, inside windows).  This is my second booking for a deep clean and my first one was much better than the second one.  
I hope that the person that will be doing a deep clean at my parents house will do a very good job.  I will find out today.
I hope to continue requesting your services, but the job has to be better.

Rating Comment:
Harbi has been assigned to our home for about three weeks and his cleaning services have declined.

These are the concerns that arose during his last visit:
-arrived without necessary cleaning products and I had to supply cleaner 
-all mirrors (bathrooms, front hall closet doors) were not cleaned
-a murky film was left on stovetop and other appliances were not wiped down 
-kitchen counters were not wiped down
-objects are moved around a lot and displaced, but dust is not picked up 
-Harbi finishes and remains an extra half hour, praying (1st week) or eating his lunch (this week), while waiting for a pick-up.  

We have been long-time bi-weekly clients.  Rates have increased and we are content to pay them.  However, we expect the full services that we pay for.  Harbi advised that he has only been working for your company for a short time.  After requesting a change from our last cleaner due to toxic chemical levels, we were assured an experienced cleaner would be assigned to our home.  This did not happen.  Please assign an experienced cleaner to our home.  Thank you.

Rating Comment: Not to single out this cleaner - he did an equivalent job to most previous cleaners. Floors were vacuumed or mopped, bathrooms were clean. But he stayed only 1.5 hours, from 8h50 to 10h20. Perhaps he works faster than others, but it does not seem sufficient for the 3h40min estimate for my house cleaning. Indeed, reviewing the list of what should be included in a regular cleaning, some things were missed... just downstairs I counted 10 cobwebs in corners and hanging from ceilings. Dusting also wasn't done most places I checked: lamps, cupboard doors, baseboards, inside door window sills. Again, not to single him out... These things were likely missed by several cleaners before him. But I would like the service standard to improve. If cleaners work fast and don't stay 3h40 min, I still expect things to be done as advertised.

Rating Comment: Very unsatisfied experience! Booked a deep cleaning but the result is extremely disappointing! As can be seen, the floor is still pretty dirty and the stain on the counter is not in anyway cleaned! The washroom floor especially does not seem to have been cleaned at all! Looks like that the work is very hastily done! Price is also not competitive. The clean cost more than $280 for the 2 bed 2 bath apartment but I've found other cleaners that were willing to do it for $197. When I contacted them if I could cancel the service so that I could use the other cleaner, they said that they would charge a 50% cancellation fee if the request is made 48 hours prior to the booked date, which is unheard of!!! And as I have said above, the quality DOESN'T MATCH THE PRICE AT ALL! The cleaner also stole the change on the counter, which shouldn't have mattered as it was supposed to be her tip anyway but it try leaves on us a really bad impression. Bad experience! Very angry! BAD BAD BAD BAD BAD BAD! Nothing except the toilet seems to have been cleaned. The toilet was indeed done very nice, but I didn't pay $280 to have someone brush my toilet!

Rating Comment:
I booked a deep clean, and some things were nicely cleaned, like inside the fridge and microwave. However, there were still cobwebs throughout the house, a dirty toilet and bathroom tiles, fingerprints on all the high-touches areas, dusty shelves and surfaces, etc. Basic things that should have been easily covered. The company was kind enough to send another cleaner. That cleaner dusted some additional surfaces, but the main issues remained - dirty toilet, tiles, cobwebs, etc. It is hard to understand how a place can be considered "clean" with so much visible grime left behind. 

I booked a deep clean to save myself time. I also thought professionals would do a better job than I could. Instead, I spent time and money, only to find myself now deep cleaning the space personally. I am very disappointed.

Rating Comment:
Your company sent only one cleaner to clean our entire home and he seemed surprised that he would have to clean our kitchen. 

I had to ask him to re-mop the hardwood floors with my own mop as it looked like he hadn’t mopped at all. He also left lots of streaks all over the silver faucets in the bathrooms and didn’t wipe down all the counters. I had to ask him to clean our shower door and to mop the floors in the bathrooms as he didn’t clean them at all. I will have to scrub the bathroom floor by the tub because it appears to have not been cleaned either. There are still marks on the tile floors after he took our mop to them (after me asking him to clean the bathroom floors). The toilet bowls exterior weren’t all cleaned either. 

Eventually we just let him leave because I didn’t think he would do a better job after asking him to re-clean those areas (some things were still missed). He missed a bunch of spots mopping, even after asking him to redo it with our proper wring-style mop. He brought a swiffer-style mop which is not acceptable for house cleaning. He didn’t move the front mat to mop under there either, it was all muddy and wet when we looked under after he left. 

We paid for spot cleaning on the walls and he didn’t do that, nor did he wipe down any of the light switches. 

We are having our house listing pictures taken tomorrow morning and so my husband and I spent the rest of the afternoon (and we will continue this evening) going over what he cleaned to make it ready by our standards. 

The cleaner seemed young and very inexperienced. He was very polite and was amenable to re-clean the areas we asked him to and to clean the stove, however, we still found his job unsatisfactory in the end. I had to wipe down all the cupboards and counters, and spot clean the walls. 

Why did you only send one cleaner for this job? Required two at the very least and one with more experience. 

I appreciate that your company is open on the weekends for cleanings as there are not many who do, but you really sent your most inexperienced cleaner today and we would not recommend your company to anyone looking.

Rating Comment:
Hi guys,

The cleaner spent 4.5 hours here today, and he did a terrible job.  We don’t want to get the poor guy in trouble, but he was wearing his BOOTS in the house the whole time. He “cleaned” the floors and they are covered in boot marks.  He also used a spray mop on our new hardwood floors (which are not to
be sprayed).  I’ve had to go back over the floors on my hands and knees because they were still filthy.  I had to wash all the walls as they were covered in dirt and dust.  He didn’t clean any of the open shelving in the living room, or mantle.  He did not clean the kitchen cabinets (which I intentionally kept empty so that they could be cleaned).  We are pretty ticked off.  

I’m getting really tired of asking this question, but what can we do about this?  We don’t want anymore people in our home, but we are not comfortable paying for what was a really terrible cleaning job.

Rating Comment: I asked for a deep clean because we are selling our home. I mentioned we had animals and that our house will definitely need the deep clean. The lady was friendly but did a very half fast job whereby she did not move any small objects to dust properly and only dusted around objects. Dusted in front of the tv but didn’t do any in back. Bathrooms were half done as the bath was cleaned but not the shower in one and then the other bathroom was cleaned except  the floor. I was told lady would have all cleaning supplies but did not as she used our vacuum and broom. When mopping the floor and instead of some scrubbing at one or two spots, she left the dirt as is. The website also said included windows and doors and baseboards and only 1 set of windows were done quickly and no doors nor baseboards. If this job needed more than one day then we would have liked to be told this when she came. We would have gladly paid for 2 days rather than 1 rushed day!

Rating Comment:
The cleaner was polite and courteous, however some areas could have been cleaned better and more supplies were needed.
I had asked/instructed to have the shower in the ensuite cleaned well. However there was still mold and streaks left in the shower after the cleaning. Since we didn't need the tub or second shower cleaned again this week - I let him know to focus his time on the one shower. So it wasn't due to lack of time. We ended up having to do a cleaning of the shower ourselves this weekend.
The cleaner asked us to provide a vacuum and paper towel (we provided a steam mop already) - which is fine, but wasn't asked for at the start of the cleaning, and gave me the sense that he wasn't prepared.
He spent less than 2.5 hours at our place, arriving at 10am (right at the end of the arrival window) and left at 12:25. Which was much less time than the 4+ hour time quoted / paid for.

The cleaning was specified as:

Deep Cleaning

Basement

The house was left covered in hair, dust, grime and caked on, oily cleaning products (toilet, desk, kitchen cupboard) where the cleaner worked however many areas were not cleaned at all (e.g. baseboards, showers, sinks, wall spots). As well, poor cleaning technique has made some areas worse than before the cleaners arrived. For example, the basement was not swept properly, so mopping afterwards left hair and fur matted on the floor such that it cannot now be easily swept away and needs to be scrubbed.

As such, I am requesting a refund.


In case there is no record on your end from the phone calls from today and yesterday here is a brief synopsis of the events:

I called UrbanMop yesterday around 4PM to request additional cleaners. My cleaner, Andrew said he was done around 2PM and asked my wife and I to spot check his work. We requested him to redo many places in the basement while we assess the upstairs. After seeing him redo work in the basement it was clear he would not be able to clean the house in time, or to quality and so we called UrbanMop for additional cleaners. We requested a deep clean with extra services as our house was being photographed the next day (today) at noon.

After our call with UrbanMop Andrew took photos to show the work he completed, at which time I asked if I could follow him and take photos as well which he agreed to. I've attached photos from walking with Andrew as well as photos afterward he finished his work around 7PM to show the lack of cleaning that was done.

I'm happy to help describe the photos and specific issues as needed. My wife also took photos and I will provide those once she returns from work.

Overall Andrew was very kind and seemed to earnestly want to help clean despite the poor cleaning results.

Rating Comment: This cleaner barely cleaned anything. He left streaks on all appliances and mirrors. My hardwood floors are sticky from whatever cleaner he used. When I came home to check while he was here he told me “your house isn’t really dirty anyway”. Every cleaner you hire says this. My house is newer but it doesn’t mean it’s clean, it’s actually very dirty. Why am I paying $300 for someone to come here and decide not to clean anything because it’s “not dirty” when it OS. He only cleaned one bathroom thoroughly. He didn’t even barely touch my second full bathroom. He also didn’t clean my second bedroom as I checked, and there’s dog hair on the floor in the corners. It’s just absolutely ridiculous that I paid for this and the job was terrible. I will NEVER hire UrbanMop again under any circumstances, the experience has been terrible

Rating Comment: The service provided by UrbanMop was far from professional. They seemed to spend an excessive amount of time cleaning areas that were not even dirty, while completely neglecting the areas we specifically requested for thorough cleaning. The biggest challenge we faced was their lack of transparency in communication and additional charges, which left much to be desired. As experts in the field, I expected them to provide an accurate time estimate before commencing the cleaning, but instead, I continuously received calls from customer service requesting approval for additional hours, causing great inconvenience. The overall customer service experience was exceptionally poor, and I would not consider using their services again nor would I recommend them to anyone. I deeply regret my decision to choose UrbanMop for our cleaning needs.

Rating Comment: I am disappointed with my experience with Urban Mop. The “move in” clean wasn’t completed as described during booking. I was also promised a team of two professional cleaners to complete this job in 5 hours which also didn’t happen. A full bathroom, the entire basement, the inside of all appliances and inside windows were NOT cleaned  in the 10 hour period. This was not acceptable as in the past I’ve had a similar size home cleaned in 6 hours. I expected that 10 hours would be more than enough time to do a “deep clean” as there was no furniture and it was not a dirty house. Next time I will go with a professional company who can provide an accurate quote and guarantee the job will be finished properly and take responsibility making that happen.

That’s why we had a cleaner come in!  A few things were not done, ie., clearing out garbage cans throughout the house, my gas stove’s over stove exhaust fan wasn’t cleaned at all.  There is still mold in the primary bathroom.  We also did not have 3 bedrooms to clean, as one of the bedrooms is used as an office and we asked the cleaner not to do anything in there.  I feel for the price charged these small items should have been done.  I have no doubt the cleaner worked very hard, which is appreciated,  We will welcome the cleaner back but want to hear what the price will be going forward.

Rating Comment:
Unfortunately it was not a great experience. Were having a Reno done to the primary bathroom  so there was no requirement to clean that bathroom, and much of the floor was covered in plastic/ paper (stairs, upstairs hallway and master bedroom. Additionally I was working in one of the bedrooms so there was no need to clean in.   I had asked that the kitchen cabinets be wiped down given that there was a lot less work to be done. The cleaner indicated that she only had time to wipe one of the cabinets and that she wouldn’t have time for the rest. I asked if she had done any additional work given that she didn’t have to clean most of the upstairs. Her response was that the one bathroom upstairs was very dirty so it took a long time to clean and that she throughly cleaned the remainder of the house. The upstairs bathroom definitely needed to be cleaned … but it wasn’t filthy.  She was also very clearly uncomfortable with the a dog in the house. 

I will say that she did a good job on what she cleaned but I was disappointed that she was unable to complete the one additional item I had asked her to. Overall it was not a great experience.

Failing this I may have to consider another option for house cleaning services. 

Sincerely,
Glenn.

Rating Comment:
I had a long conversation with “Ce” ( hope that is correct). The lady who arrived to clean worked hard enough but cleaning was so inappropriate. She arrived with a carry bag which included all her products. Before she started she asked me for a bucket. I didn’t have anything as my daughter has not moved in yet. As a result there was no warm, soapy water used for anything. She had a spray bottle with water and a cleaning product in it. ( I believe it was just water). She had a rag mop that she used on all three levels without even rinsing it- all hardwood floors. She also had an electric broom that she used as a vacuum cleaner!!!! Mostly she seemed to use paper towels too. Clean. There was no evidence of cloth rags! In my original conversation with you before booking I inquired if you use environment friendly products and was told yes. When I asked this cleaner she was very surprised. She quickly said told me that she has not met or spoken to anyone from Urban Mop!!! She is contracted by your company by email when they need her. This made me very uneasy knowing there is no screening of personnel, no specific training either. All in all I was extremely disappointed. How you could expect someone without a car even function in this capacity is mind boggling. No wonder she didn’t have a vacuum!!! Arrangements have been made for a repeat cleaning on Tue and I will be watching very carefully!!!!!!        
Jane McBride
